- Added support for running Fleet against MySQL 9.6 and 9.7 LTS by computing all checksum/token hashes in Go instead of using the `MD5()`/`SHA1()` SQL functions, which those versions removed. Existing hash values are preserved, so upgrades do not trigger profile re-delivery or DDM re-sync. **Upgrade ordering:** when moving an existing deployment to MySQL 9.6/9.7, upgrade Fleet first and then MySQL. Upgrading Fleet runs a migration that removes the last `MD5()` references from the schema; if MySQL is upgraded first, the still-present `MD5()`-based generated columns will break writes until Fleet is upgraded.

